# Security Constraints — GC Hook

- ONLY permitted technique: DLL proxy replacing steam_api64.dll + ISteamGameCoordinator vtable hook
- PROHIBITED: direct memory scanning, ReadProcessMemory/WriteProcessMemory, code injection into running processes, kernel-mode drivers
- The proxy DLL must forward ALL non-GC calls to the original DLL unchanged
- GC message modification is limited to injecting CSOEconItem entries into SOCache responses
- Never modify SendMessage (outgoing GC messages) — only RetrieveMessage (incoming)
- Item IDs must use high ranges (> 2^40) to avoid conflicts with real items
- The hook must be completely removable by restoring the original DLL
